                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/33994: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-26T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 26, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1033. In view of the reply made by Molotov to your questions regarding the Polish
                    underground reported in your 1343, April 18, there would appear to be no further
                    action which you should take in this matter for the time being. We have been
                    informed by London that five leaders of the Polish underground have recently
                    arrived at Bari from where they are being brought to England for questioning by
                    the British authorities on conditions inside Poland. Any information received
                    from this source which tends to confirm the claims of the Polish Government will
                    be communicated to you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
